OL,3,CBoy with autism and 'strong
OL,4,Cattraction' to water drowned after
OL,5,Crunning away
OL,7,FMr Howe said: "We think it is likely
OL,8,Fthat he made his way directly to the
OL,9,Friver and as he has done in the past,
OL,10,Fentered the water impulsively without
OL,11,Frealising the danger."
OL,13,FHe described Luke as a 'joyful' boy
OL,14,Fwho would speak to everyone he met and
OL,15,Floved the fantasy series Harry Potter.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/10
